entry.tran: 打开（箱、盒等）；（从箱、盒等中）取出
entry.def: When you unpack a suitcase, box, or similar container, or you unpack the things inside it, you take the things out of the container.

example.ex: Our guide unpacked a picnic of ham sandwiches and offered us tea.
example.tran: 我们的导游打开装着火腿三明治的野餐盒，并给我们倒了些茶水。

entry.def: If you unpack an idea or problem, you analyse it and consider it in detail.

example.ex: A lot of ground has been covered in unpacking the issues central to achieving this market-led strategic change.
example.tran: 在分析实现这个以市场为导向的战略转变的关键问题时，涉及了诸多领域。
